t:29px;text-align:left;"><p style=3D"margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0"></p><p s=
tyle=3D"margin:10px 0">I entered a massive SL on this one a few months back=
 and it is doing well. We knew there would be a shortage for the next 5 yea=
rs or more w the electrification of the world but now it is next level.  Su=
lphuric acid shortage was NOT on my bingo card. </p><p style=3D"margin:10px=
 0">The main reason is fear of a supply shortage. Traders are also betting =
that demand for copper will stay strong in the future. A key problem is the=
 disruption in the Middle East. Since March, the U.S.-Iran conflict has sev=
erely reduced exports of sulphur and sulphuric acid from the region.</p><p =
style=3D"margin:10px 0">That matters because sulphuric acid is used in copp=
er processing. It helps refiners extract and purify copper before turning i=
t into anodes, which are a key step in producing usable copper.  Because su=
lphuric acid has become harder to get, China has stopped exporting it. This=
 has made the shortage worse.</p><p style=3D"margin:10px 0">Chile, the worl=
d=E2=80=99s biggest copper producer, has also been hit. Some major copper r=
efiners there have had to reduce production, which means less copper is ava=
ilable.</p><p></p></div></td></tr>
